T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 418
EP  - 426
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Much organizational theory and research is characterized by an uncritical acceptance of the efficacy of open communication. In this critique, the lack of support for this view of openness is discussed. A contingency perspective that more accurately reflects the political nature of organizational life is proposed.
AB  - Much organizational theory and research is characterized by an uncritical acceptance of the efficacy of open communication. In this critique, the lack of support for this view of openness is discussed. A contingency perspective that more accurately reflects the political nature of organizational life is proposed.
