TY  - JOUR
T1  - Employee Perspectives on Stock Ownership: Financial Investment or Mechanism of Control?
AU  - Lawrence, French J.
Y1  - 1987/07/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1987.4306558
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1987.4306558
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 427
EP  - 435
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper explores employee ownership as a financial investment rather than a mechanism of control. Viewed from such a perspective, relations among employee ownership, satisfaction, and desired influence are more complex than supposed. Employee owners' satisfaction with the firm and their jobs depends, in part, on their perceptions of the firm's financial performance and of the effectiveness of other employees. Dissatisfaction may increase efforts by employee owners to influence decision making.
AB  - This paper explores employee ownership as a financial investment rather than a mechanism of control. Viewed from such a perspective, relations among employee ownership, satisfaction, and desired influence are more complex than supposed. Employee owners' satisfaction with the firm and their jobs depends, in part, on their perceptions of the firm's financial performance and of the effectiveness of other employees. Dissatisfaction may increase efforts by employee owners to influence decision making.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1987.4306558
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1987.4306558
Y2  - 2026/04/24
